es working around the tailgate, looking down into the cargo area with a patient, caretaker-like expression. Inside the wagon, several animals are now visible in the back, including woolly, goat-like or sheep-like forms with horns and shaggy coats packed under the roof.\n\nA wider view shows the full wagon parked beside a sloping rock face, with animals gathered around it. On the rocky hillside above are several camels and smaller animals; nearer the car are larger animals, including what appears to be an elephant and other dark, bulky shapes. The elderly man stands at the right side of the car near a ramp or tailgate platform, dwarfed by the station wagon and the animals around it. He then reaches up and handles a large long-necked bird or birdlike animal, grasping it around the body and neck as he guides it upward. The animal’s long neck bends and sways while he lifts and steadies it, his face partly hidden behind the animal as he works.\n\nMore animals crowd the ramp. Two striped tigers move across the wooden boards near the rear of the wagon, one darker and one lighter in tone, their long bodies filling the space as they step carefully past the man. Their striped flanks pass close together, tails low, while a large elephant stands in the background on the rocks. The man remains behind them, visible between their bodies, calm and watchful as they board.\n\nAt the side of the wagon, the man stands beside a rear side window. His white-bearded face is reflected in the glass. An animal’s head or neck passes between him and the car, briefly brushing close to the window, and he looks at it with a small, amused smile. A large pale animal then crosses very close in front of him, its body filling the view and momentarily obscuring his face. When the animal passes, the man looks upward again, as if checking the next creature in line.\n\nA camel approaches from the right, towering above the man and the car. The man stands below it, one arm raised, gesturing for it to move forward. Its long neck and legs dominate the scene as it steps toward the ramp. The man’s face appears beneath the animal’s body as it passes overhead, then a large hoofed foot lands on the wooden boards. The boards flex visually under the weight, emphasizing the heavy load being taken into or over the wagon’s rear area. The man looks serious and focused, continuing to guide the boarding process.\n\nWith the animals loaded, the man moves to the back of the station wagon and swings the large tailgate closed. From a low angle, he pushes the pale rear door upward and then presses it firmly into place with both hands, patting and smoothing the outside as if making sure everything is secure. He smiles as he finishes, then steps away from the rear.\n\nInside the front of the car, the driver’s area is crowded with animals. A young big cat sits near the steering wheel and dashboard, its paws up on the seat or console, while another animal’s head is partly visible beside it. The dashboard has a large round steering wheel and circular gauges. The elderly man leans in from the driver’s side, bending around the animals to get into position. He settles behind the wheel, reaching forward with one hand, while the animals shift in the passenger area beside him. Outside the windshield, the rocky hillside is visible, making the car still feel parked in the same wild, outdoor setting.\n\nThe commercial then returns to exterior views of the station wagon. The front grille and stacked headlamps are shown prominently, then the long side of the car passes by, highlighting the length of the body, the chrome trim, the large side panels, and the whitewall tires. The wagon moves through a wooded area, partly hidden by branches and leaves in the foreground. Animals remain around it, including bulky silhouettes near the car, while the vehicle continues away through rough ground and trees.\n\nFinally, the wagon is seen from behind driving along a narrow, wooded path, receding into the distance under overhanging branches. Large white block letters appear across the lower part of the screen reading “THE 1967 AMERICAN MOTORS.” The car continues away behind the text, its pale rear and long roofline still visible as it disappears deeper into the sepia-toned woods.",
